headline: DoorDash exits 4 markets, including Japan, to focus on growth elsewhere
summary: DoorDash said Wednesday that it’s ending operations in Qatar, Singapore, Japan and Uzbekistan.  The San Francisco-based delivery company said the decision comes after a monthslong review of country-specific conditions.  DoorDash said it wants to focus its investments on places were it can build sustainable scale and long-term market leadership.

headline: Nvidia Earnings Slam Into Market With No Patience for AI Hiccups
summary: “Even if they have tremendous numbers, we know the markets are really fickle,” said Ken Mahoney, president of Mahoney Asset Management.  After powering the market higher for much of the past few years, Nvidia shares have gone cold in recent months, rising just 3.8% since the start of the fourth quarter, as investors question the hundreds of billions of dollars customers like Alphabet Inc. and Microsoft Corp. are spending on AI.

headline: Why OpenTable, Resy and DoorDash are fighting for your reservation
summary: Founded in 1998, OpenTable went relatively unchallenged in the online reservation space for more than a decade. Its dominance was disrupted by Resy, which targeted highly sought-after restaurants by undercutting OpenTable on pricing and offering more advanced software. OpenTable has since revamped its business model and partnered with Visa and Chase to better compete with American Express-backed Resy and new entrants like DoorDash.
